commentTextItems.html: hammered over extra cover and to the rope and Scotland win by 8 wickets

commentPostTextItems.html: So Scotland roundly hammer Ireland to secure a consolation win. For the home side it's a rare defeat to a fellow associate but they do take the series 2-1.
Craig Young has been named as man of the series after taking 9 wickets for 135.
Thanks for following our coverage of the games throughout and from Conor Hayes in a sunny Malahide, it's goodbye.

milestones.description: Calum MacLeod and Gardiner's 179-run partnership is SCOT's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 144 between Calum MacLeod and Matt Machan
Kevin O'Brien has scored 12 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for IRE breaking Porterfield's record
Craig Young has taken the most five-wicket hauls (1) in ODIs for IRE, going past vd Merwe's record
Josh Davey has taken the most five-wicket hauls (1) in ODIs for SCOT, going past Gordon Goudie's record
